hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Growth law at $R=R_{typ}=\alpha R_c$:
$$
\frac{dR}{dt}\Big|_{R=\alpha R_c}
= \frac{K_0}{R_c(\alpha R_c)} - \frac{K_0}{(\alpha R_c)^2}
= \frac{K_0}{R_c^2}\left(\frac{1}{\alpha} - \frac{1}{\alpha^2}\right)
= \frac{K_0}{R_c^2}\,\frac{\alpha-1}{\alpha^2}.
$$

2. Self-similarity gives
$$
\frac{dR_{typ}}{dt}
=\alpha\,\frac{dR_c}{dt}
= \frac{K_0}{R_c^2}\,\frac{\alpha-1}{\alpha^2}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
\frac{dR_c}{dt}
= \frac{K_0}{R_c^2}\,\frac{\alpha-1}{\alpha^3}.
$$

3. Coarsening rate 
$$
\mathcal K=\frac{d(R_c^3)}{dt}
=3R_c^2\,\frac{dR_c}{dt}
=3R_c^2\cdot\frac{K_0}{R_c^2}\,\frac{\alpha-1}{\alpha^3}
=3\frac{\alpha-1}{\alpha^3}K_0.
$$
